// NOTE: Integrated into the Fusion FSN tree for migration traceability.
// CONTENT:
// Product Info Sheet: Fusion FluxExecutive SummaryFusion Flux is the static analysis engine and linter for the Fusion ecosystem. While standard linters (Clippy, Pylint, Clang-Tidy) check language syntax, Flux checks Architecture. It validates Fusion.toml manifests against runtime capabilities, detects blocking I/O operations that would stall the Supernova reactor, and ensures FFI boundaries between languages are safe.Product IdentityName: Fusion FluxCLI Command: fluxConfiguration: Flux.toml (optional) or [linter] section in Fusion.toml.Core Philosophy: "Catch architectural drift before it compiles."Key CapabilitiesRuntime Compatibility Check: Ensures your code doesn't use features unsupported by your target (e.g., importing Python libraries when targeting v1 Native).Reactor Safety: Scans Rust source code for blocking standard library calls (like std::fs::read or std::thread::sleep) that would freeze the async HyperRing.Polyglot Consistency: Validates that C++ header files defined in Fusion.toml actually exist and match the declared FFI bindings in Rust.Auto-Fix: Automatically refactors common anti-patterns (e.g., swapping std::thread::sleep for fusion_rt::time::sleep).Target AudienceFusion Developers: Ensuring their hybrid apps run efficiently on the Supernova mesh.CI/CD Pipelines: Gating commits that violate architectural constraints.
